laboratory_examinations.findings: There are multiple shadowing stones within a relatively contracted gallbladder. The common bile duct measures 5 mm. The liver is normal in shape and contour with normal echogenicity. No focal hepatic masses. The portal vein is patent. No intrahepatic biliary dilation. The pancreas is not well evaluated. The spleen is normal and measures 11.9 cm. Bilateral kidneys are unremarkable, left kidney measures 10.5 cm, right kidney measures 12.5 cm.
